Core Rules

1.Always maintain a dark mode aesthetic consistent with OKX's branding
2.Prioritize responsive design that works across all device sizes
3.Follow React best practices with functional components and hooks
4.Keep bundle size minimal by avoiding unnecessary dependencies
5.Implement proper error handling for all API interactions
6.Ensure authentication flows are secure and intuitive
7.Use CSS modules or styled-components for styling components
8.Follow atomic design principles for component organization
9.Include subtle animations for interactive elements (trading charts, buttons)
10.Implement proper loading states for async operations

